Description: Fragment of stemmed foot of East Greek (North Ionian?) pottery cup; pale orange clay with white inclusions and some silver mica; wholly glazed, save for stand surface and inside of stem; inscription cut on stand surface.
Bibliographic references: Petrie 1886 / Naukratis. Part I., 1884-85 (pl. XXXIV, no. 471)
Bernand 1970 / Le Delta égyptien d'après les textes grecs, i: les confins libyques (p. 673, no. 317)
Villing et al 2013-2015 / Naukratis: Greeks in Egypt (GG.376)
